abstract: The candidates must know the quirks of California’s vast political geography.
snippet: The candidates must know the quirks of California’s vast political geography.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Welcome, Democrats and debate spinners, to the city with a Mexican-American-Jewish-Italian Rhodes Scholar mayor, who is not running for president, in the state with an Irish Catholic governor who surely is, just not this time.

abstract: In the changing suburbs of Bucks County in Pennsylvania, where traditional party allegiances are scrambled, voters viewed impeachment through the prism of President Trump.
snippet: In the changing suburbs of Bucks County in Pennsylvania, where traditional party allegiances are scrambled, voters viewed impeachment through the prism of President Trump.
lead_paragraph: BUCKINGHAM TOWNSHIP, Pa. — Treacy Broadhead, a registered Republican, has voted in recent years for all of her party’s candidates for office, save one: Donald J. Trump.

abstract: Tariffs and trade tensions are a huge source of worry for U.S. companies, with nearly half of Fortune 500 companies referencing such concerns during last quarter's earnings calls, the U.S. Chamber of Commerce said on Thursday.
snippet: Tariffs and trade tensions are a huge source of worry for U.S. companies, with nearly half of Fortune 500 companies referencing such concerns during last quarter's earnings calls, the U.S. Chamber of Commerce said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Tariffs and trade tensions are a huge source of worry for U.S. companies, with nearly half of Fortune 500 companies referencing such concerns during last quarter's earnings calls, the U.S. Chamber of Commerce said on Thursday.
headline_main: Tariffs, Trade Tensions Worry Fortune 500 CEOs: U.S. Chamber of Commerce
headline_print_headline: Tariffs, Trade Tensions Worry Fortune 500 CEOs: U.S. Chamber of Commerce

abstract: Elizabeth Warren has recalibrated her rhetoric on Medicare for All, as concerns about her support for replacing private insurance with a government-run plan continue to buffet her once-surging Democratic presidential campaign.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren has recalibrated her rhetoric on Medicare for All, as concerns about her support for replacing private insurance with a government-run plan continue to buffet her once-surging Democratic presidential campaign.
lead_paragraph: CLINTON, Iowa — Elizabeth Warren has recalibrated her rhetoric on Medicare for All, as concerns about her support for replacing private insurance with a government-run plan continue to buffet her once-surging Democratic presidential campaign.
headline_main: Seeking Fresh Momentum, Democrat Warren Recalibrates 'Medicare for All' Rhetoric
headline_print_headline: Seeking Fresh Momentum, Democrat Warren Recalibrates 'Medicare for All' Rhetoric

abstract: A U.S. appeals court ruled on Wednesday that a component of the Obamacare law is unconstitutional, but dodged a major ruling by stopping short of declaring that the rest of the landmark 2010 healthcare statute must also be struck down.
snippet: A U.S. appeals court ruled on Wednesday that a component of the Obamacare law is unconstitutional, but dodged a major ruling by stopping short of declaring that the rest of the landmark 2010 healthcare statute must also be struck down.

headline_main: U.S. Appeals Court Sidesteps Major Obamacare Ruling

abstract: On a day when the U.S. House of Representatives debated whether President Donald Trump should be removed from office, members of his administration fanned out across the country to make the case that the president is steadily getting the job done.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — On a day when the U.S. House of Representatives debated whether President Donald Trump should be removed from office, members of his administration fanned out across the country to make the case that the president is steadily getting the job done.
headline_main: As Impeachment Looms, Trump Officials Look to Change the Subject
headline_print_headline: As Impeachment Looms, Trump Officials Look to Change the Subject

abstract: One day after House Republicans stood in unanimous opposition to impeachment, Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell positioned his GOP-controlled chamber to second the party's unapologetic embrace of President Donald Trump, putting the president's effective takeover of the party on stark display.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — One day after House Republicans stood in unanimous opposition to impeachment, Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell positioned his GOP-controlled chamber to second the party's unapologetic embrace of President Donald Trump, putting the president's effective takeover of the party on stark display.
headline_main: GOP Embraces Trump as Never Before With Anti-Impeachment
headline_print_headline: GOP Embraces Trump as Never Before With Anti-Impeachment
